com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.network.shared

Interface Callback<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The Type of Object, this Callback expects.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.function.Consumer<T>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Callback<T>
extends java.util.function.Consumer<T>
    This Callback is used for latching onto the ReceivingService and SendingService.

    It will listen to something, in respect to the Service it was added to.

    Since:
    1.0
    Version:

    • Method Detail

      • isAcceptable

        default boolean isAcceptable(T t)
        This method might be overridden to say, whether or not this specific Callback will accept an element which it should handle.

        It checks against null by default.

        Parameters:
        t - the Object of the specified type T.
        Returns:
        true, if this Callback will handle the object, else false.

      • isRemovable

        default boolean isRemovable()
        This method tells the encapsulating Class, whether or not it can be removed.

        By default, it states true and will be removed, on the first check.

        Returns:
        boolean value, if this Callback can be cleaned up or not.

      • onRemove

        default void onRemove()
        This method might be overridden to react, if and when this Callback is removed wherever it is held.

        By default, this method does nothing!

      • onError

        default void onError()
        This method might be overridden to react if an error occurs.

        By default, this method does nothing!
